======================================================================
PALEY PERFECT ALIGNMENT: PROOF SKETCH
======================================================================

  CLAIM: At p=3 mod 4, the Paley orientation achieves PERFECT ALIGNMENT:
    all non-zero Walsh coefficients h_hat[S] * prod_{i in S} sigma_P[i] > 0.

  MECHANISM:
  1. The Paley orientation has sigma_i = chi(i+1) where chi is the
     Legendre symbol (QR -> +1, NQR -> -1).

  2. For a Walsh coefficient h_hat[S] with |S|=d, the sign at Paley is:
     sign = sign(h_hat[S]) * prod_{i in S} chi(i+1)
          = sign(h_hat[S]) * chi(prod_{i in S}(i+1))

  3. If h_hat[S] = f(|prod gaps|) * chi(prod gaps), then
     sign = sign(f) * chi(prod)^2 = sign(f) > 0  (assuming f > 0)

  This works iff the Walsh coefficient has the form:
     h_hat[S] = |c(S)| * chi(prod_{i in S}(i+1))

  i.e., the sign of h_hat is the Legendre symbol of the product of gaps.

  VERIFICATION:

  p=7:
    S={0, 1}: h=     +3.50, prod_gaps=2, chi=+1, sign(h)=+1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 2}: h=     -3.50, prod_gaps=3, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    S={1, 2}: h=     -3.50, prod_gaps=6, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    *** ALL WALSH COEFFICIENTS MATCH: sign(h) = chi(prod gaps) ***

  p=11:
    S={0, 1}: h=     -8.25, prod_gaps=2, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 1, 2, 3}: h=   -118.25, prod_gaps=2, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 1, 2, 4}: h=   -118.25, prod_gaps=8, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 1, 3, 4}: h=   -118.25, prod_gaps=7, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 2}: h=   +272.25, prod_gaps=3, chi=+1, sign(h)=+1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 2, 3, 4}: h=   +118.25, prod_gaps=5, chi=+1, sign(h)=+1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 3}: h=   +272.25, prod_gaps=4, chi=+1, sign(h)=+1 [MATCH]
    S={0, 4}: h=     +8.25, prod_gaps=5, chi=+1, sign(h)=+1 [MATCH]
    S={1, 2}: h=   -272.25, prod_gaps=6, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    S={1, 2, 3, 4}: h=   -118.25, prod_gaps=10, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
    S={1, 3}: h=     -8.25, prod_gaps=8, chi=-1, sign(h)=-1 [MATCH]
